nd%20energy%20prices%2C%20also%20accelerated%203.8%25%20year-per-year%2C%20higher%20than%20the%203.7%25%20print%20economists%20had%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStubborn%20inflation%20is%20fueling%20fear%20that%20the%20Fed%20could%20keep%20interest%20rates%20higher%20for%20longer%2C%20though%20investors%20had%20initially%20priced%20in%20hefty%20rate%20cuts%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20Markets%20are%20now%20pricing%20in%20just%20a%206%25%20chance%20the%20Fed%20could%20cut%20interest%20rates%20by%20100%20points%20or%20more%20this%20year%2C%20down%20from%20a%2061%25%20chance%20priced%20in%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CME%20FedWatch%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20odds%20of%20a%20June%20Fed%20rate%20cut%20have%20been%20completely%20wiped%20off%20the%20table.%20Investors%20are%20pricing%20in%20a%200%25%20chance%20of%20a%20rate%20cut%20that%20month%2C%20compared%20to%20a%2057%25%20chance%20priced%20in%20a%20month%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20kiss%20a%20June%20rate%20cut%20goodbye%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20Bankrate's%20chief%20financial%20analyst%2C%20said%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20improvement%20here%2C%20we're%20moving%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%20of%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20CPI%20report%20may%20have%20even%20dashed%20the%20odds%20of%20a%20July%20Fed%20rate%20cut%20off%20the%20table%2C%20according%20to%20Seema%20Shah%2C%20the%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20Principal%20Asset%20Management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20marks%20the%20third%20consecutive%20strong%20reading%20and%20means%20that%20the%20stalled%20disinflationary%20narrative%20can%20no%20longer%20be%20called%20a%20blip.%20In%20fact%2C%20even%20if%20inflation%20were%20to%20cool%20next%20month%20to%20a%20more%20comfortable%20reading%2C%20there%20is%20likely%20sufficient%20caution%20within%20the%20Fed%20now%20to%20mean%20that%20a%20July%20cut%20may%20also%20