ave%20reasons%20for%20our%20small%20family.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Laura%20Amoriello)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonly-child-parent-wish-people-less-judgmental-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fighter%20pilots%20can%20black%20out%20in%20seconds%20during%20high-G%20flying.%20Here's%20how%20flight%20experts%20say%20they%20train%20to%20stay%20conscious.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22F-35A%20Lighting%20II%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66159e8a1caec1275a6e4b9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224584%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaj.%20Kristin%20%26quot%3BBEO%26quot%3B%20Wolfe%20demonstrates%20the%20capabilities%20of%20the%20F-35A%20Lighting%20II%2C%20a%20single%20seat%2C%20single%20engine%2C%20all-weather%20stealth%20multirole%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20during%20a%20practice%20flight%20with%20the%20F-35%20Demonstration%20Team%20at%20Hill%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Utah%2C%20Dec.%2013%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EJack%20Rodgers%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAir%20Force%20pilots%20are%20extensively%20trained%20to%20prevent%20loss%20of%20consciousness%20during%20high-acceleration%20flights.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Anti-G%20Straining%20Maneuver%20helps%20pilots%20maintain%20consciousness%20when%20they%20fly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETechnology%20such%20as%20the%20Automatic%20Ground%20Collision%20Avoidance%20System%20have%20reduced%20G-LOC%20accidents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20flying%20a%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20and%20you%20are%20accelerating.%20But%20you're%20relaxed%20%E2%80%94%20a%20little%20too%20relaxed.%20Suddenly%2C%20you%20notice%20your%20peripheral%20vision%20beginning%20to%20fade.%20In%20what%20may%20be%20just%20seconds%2C%20you%20completely%20lose%20consciousness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20G-LOC%2C%20or%20G-induced%20loss%20of%20consciousness%2C%20and%20the%20results%20can%20be%20catastrophic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20flight%2C%20levels%20of%20acceleration%20known%20as%20G-force%20vary%2C%20and%20when%20pilots%20experience%20its%20highest%20levels%2C%20the%20pressure%20of%20gravity%20pushes%20blood%20to%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20human%20body%2C%20causing%20low%20blood%20circulation%20in%20the%20upper%20half%20of%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20that%20happens%20for%20an%20extended%20enough%20period%20of%20time%2C%20you%20will%20lose%20consciousness%2C%26quot%3B%20Lt.%20Col.%20Carolyn%20Price%20Moore%2C%20an%20aerospace%20physiologist%20and%20the%20chief%20of%20the%2019th%20Air%20Force's%20Aircrew%20Performance%20Branch%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20pilots%20must%20prepare%20their%20bodies%20for%20the%20reaction%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20acceleration%20during%20their%20flights.%20Experts%20broke%20down%20how%20pilots%20make%20it%20through%20these%20high-pressure%20endeavors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20T-38%20Talon%20aircraft%20flying%20from%20Columbus%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Ohio.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6438c08ff62706001942f4ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20T-38%20Talon%20aircraft%20flying%20from%20Columbus%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Ohio.%3Cp%3EAirman%20First%20Class%20Thomas%20Sjoberg%2FDVIDS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20training%20that%20we%20do%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20pilot%20is%20capable%20of%20doing%20the%20maneuver%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20Moore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Anti-G%20Straining%20Maneuver%2C%20also%20known%20as%20AGSM%2C%20is%20an%20exercise%20pilots%20use%20during%20high%20levels%20of%20G-force%20to%20prevent%20G-LOC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20pilots%20are%20taught%20about%20G-forces%2C%20AGSM%2C%20and%20all%20the%20ways%20that%20increased%20altitude%20and%20pressure%20can%20affect%20the%20body%20as%20early%20as%20their%20first%20week%20of%20training%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearning%20the%20ropes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20pilots%20are%20just%20starting%20out%2C%20their%20introduction%20to%20G-force%20is%20gradual.%20This%20gives%20them%20time%20to%20build%20the%20physical%20fitness%20to%20withstand%20pulling%20Gs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20really%20just%20want%20your%20lower%20body%20to%20be%20very%20strong%2C%20so%20if%20you%20can%20do%20working%20out%20that%20improves%20your%20lower%20body%20strength%20that's%20gonna%20go%20a%20long%20way%20towards%20helping%20with%20G%20tolerance%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20Moore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletes%20tend%20to%20have%20an%20advantage%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20preparing%20for%20high-G-force%20flights%20as%20they%20may%20already%20have%20significant%20lower%20body%20strength.%20Although%20height%20is%20beyond%20the%20pilot's%20control%2C%20it%20also%20helps%20to%20have%20a%20short%20stature%20as%20blood%20can%20circulate%20in%20the%20body%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20are%20put%20through%20an%20introductory%20primary%20acceleration%20training%20where%20they%20are%20individually%20spun%20in%20a%20human%20centrifuge%20that%20gradually%20increases%20in%20Gs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20nice%20slight%2C%20just%20kind%20of%20slow%20climb%20up%20into%20the%20G%20realm%20that%20lets%20them%20kind%20of%20get%20used%20to%20the%20feel%20of%20the%20centrifuge%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Senior%20Master%20Sgt.%20Tyler%20Long%2C%20who%20has%20overseen%20training%20performance%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20called%20the%20training%20a%20%26quot%3Broller%20coaster%20on%20steroids%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20%26quot%3Bit's%20a%20feeling%20you've%20never%20felt%20before%20in%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20wear%20G-suits%20that%20act%20as%20an%20external%20%26quot%3Bair%20bladder%2C%26quot%3B%20squeezing%20the%20lower%20body%20to%20promote%20blood%20flow%20if%20a%20student%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20lower%20body%20strength%20to%20flex%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22centrifuge%20spins%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615841116bde8d4ead702e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222256%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20711th%20Human%20Performance%20Wing's%20centrifuge%20spins%20with%20a%20test%20subject%20inside%20July%2014%2C%202021.%20The%20Leadership%20Dayton%20class%20was%20shown%20the%20centrifuge%20in%20action%20while%20staff%20discussed%20the%20research%20and%20training%20accomplished%20by%20the%20wing.%3Cp%3ER.J.%20Oriez%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20also%20includes%20what%20Long%20describes%20as%20the%20Sakhalin%20profile%2C%20a%20simulation%20in%20which%20the%20student%20has%20to%20track%20an%20aircraft%20onscreen%20while%20they%20undergo%20and%20ride%20out%20varying%20levels%20of%20G-force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20point%20is%20proficiency.%20Get%20them%20proficient%20with%20this%20G%20strength%2C%20get%20them%20comfortable%20to%20a%20point%20where%20they%20can%20now%20go%20and%20fly%20a%20higher%20G%20capable%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Air%20Force%20pilots%20have%20typically%20started%20out%20flying%20a%20T-1%20Jayhawk%20trainer%2C%20but%20this%20aircraft%20is%20in%20the%20process%20being%20retired%20for%20undergraduate%20pilot%20training%20and%20has%20been%20replaced%20with%20an%20Air%20Mobility%20Fundamentals-Simulator.%20The%20student%20will%20use%20this%20simulator%20for%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20undergraduate%20pilot%20will%20then%20move%20to%20fly%20a%20T-6%20Texan%20II%20aircraft%20within%20about%20seven%20months%20in%20Undergraduate%20Pilot%20Training%20and%20move%20forward%20to%20either%20mobility%20or%20heavy%20aircraft%20training%20using%20the%20AMF-Simulator%20or%20fighter%20and%20bomber%20training%20in%20a%20T-38%20Talon%20aircraft.%20Students%20are%20assigned%20an%20aircraft%20by%20the%20end%20of%20UPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20student%20masters%20this%20training%20they%20will%20fly%20the%20aircraft%20they%20were%20assigned%20and%20master%20it%20during%20the%20Formal%20Training%20Unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHandling%20the%20real%20thing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20main%20mechanisms%20of%20AGSM%20that%20prevent%20a%20pilot%20from%20passing%20out%20are%20calculated%20breathing%20and%20the%20squeezing%20of%20the%20lower%20body.%20It's%20a%20simple%20but%20life-saving%20maneuver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pilot%20even%20enters%20G-force%20onset%20while%20flying%2C%20they%20have%20to%20flex%20their%20lower%20body%20like%20their%20glutes%2C%20hamstrings%20and%20other%20muscles%20as%20tight%20as%20they%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20just%20tighten%20and%20hold%20and%20what%20that%20does%20is%20it%20actually%20compresses%20all%20of%20the%20blood%20vessels%2C%20all%20your%20veins%20and%20arteries%20in%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20your%20body%20to%20help%20prevent%20that%20pooling%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20Moore%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20flexing%20allows%20the%20blood%20to%20stay%20and%20continue%20circulating%20the%20upper%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20T-1%20Jayhawk%2C%20T-6%20Texan%20II%2C%20and%20T-38%20Talon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624dd207f0e4a00018c3e14d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20T-1%20Jayhawk%2C%20T-6%20Texan%20II%2C%20and%20T-38%20Talon%20in%20a%20dissimilar%20formation%20typically%20flown%20during%20Undergraduate%20Pilot%20Training%20graduation%20ceremonies%2C%20near%20Laughlin%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Texas%2C%20May%2017%2C%202018.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%2FSenior%20Airman%20Moshe%20Paul%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20challenging%20step%20is%20executing%20the%20proper%20breathing%20technique.%20This%20allows%20blood%20flow%20to%20return%20to%20the%20heart%20and%20then%20to%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20pilot%20should%20take%20a%20big%20deep%20breath%2C%20holding%20the%20air%20in%20their%20glottis%2C%20which%20is%20located%20in%20the%20throat%2C%20before%20the%20G-onset%20or%20acceleration%20occurs%20and%20then%20they%20begin%20the%20%26quot%3Bair%20exchange.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20air%20exchange%20is%20the%20quick%20release%20of%20air%20that%20should%20occur%20every%20three%20seconds.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20normal%20breath%2C%20it's%20a%20forced%20air%20exchange%20where%20you%20are%20essentially%20forcing%20the%20glottis%20open%20and%20closed%20really%2C%20really%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20Moore%20described.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sound%20of%20an%20air%20exchange%20sounds%20hoarse%2C%20like%20a%20mix%20between%20a%20gasp%20and%20a%20cough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20training%2C%20this%20is%20all%20done%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20the%20instructor%20who%20is%20accompanying%20the%20student%20in%20the%20aircraft.%20They%20must%20listen%20for%20the%20air%20exchanges%20to%20ensure%20and%20approve%20whether%20the%20pilot%20is%20breathing%20correctly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAccidents%20still%20happen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20G-induced%20loss%20of%20consciousness%20cannot%20be%20avoided%20and%20a%20pilot%20might%20also%20experience%20symptoms%20such%20as%20brief%20amnesia%2C%20nausea%2C%20disorientation%2C%20and%20confusion%2C%20as%20well%20as%20neck%20and%20back%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlight%20accidents%20have%20also%20occurred%20as%20a%20result%20of%20pilots%20passing%20out.%20For%20instance%2C%20among%20other%20incidents%2C%20both%20the%20Navy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdefensetech%2F2008%2F01%2F14%2Fblue-angel-crash-blamed-on-gloc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlue%20Angels%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Air%20Force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airforcetimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-air-force%2F2018%2F10%2F16%2Freport-thunderbirds-pilot-killed-in-crash-lost-consciousness-in-high-g-maneuver%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThunderbirds%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20lost%20demonstration%20pilots%20to%20G-LOC.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20many%20military%20aircraft%20are%20now%20equipped%20with%20an%20Automatic%20Ground%20Collision%20Avoidance%20System%20that%20help%20to%20prevent%20accidents%20from%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20auto%20GCAS%20is%20engaged%2C%20the%20aircraft%20itself%20gets%20texts%20if%20it%20is%20essentially%20too%20close%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20the%20aircraft%20itself%20will%20take%20over%20and%20do%20what's%20called%20a%20'fly%20up%2C'%20and%20we'll%20fly%20the%20aircraft%20back%20up%20to%20a%20safe%20altitude%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20Moore%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20installation%20of%20auto%20GCAS%20we%20have%20had%20far%20fewer%20incidents%20of%20G-induced%20loss%20of%20consciousness%20mishaps%20or%20accidents%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Boperationally%2C%20the%20auto%20GCAS%20has%20kind%20of%20been%20a%20game-changer%20in%20terms%20of%20G-LOC%20mishaps%2C%20so%20there's%20that%20guardrail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20with%20a%20kind%20of%20safety%20net%20in%20the%20aircraft%2C%20that%20doesn't%20make%20it%20any%20less%20necessary%20for%20US%20military%20pilots%20to%20train%20as%20if%20they%20don't%20and%20ready%20their%20bodies%20for%20the%20intense%20high-pressure%20challenges%20of%20high-G%20flying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-pilots-prepare-for-high-g-force-flights-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17127495020