During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20worked%20from%20home%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20I%20suddenly%20had%20way%20more%20time%20without%20long%20meetings%20or%20distractions%20that%20came%20with%20working%20in%20the%20office.%20I%20decided%20to%20spend%20my%20extra%20time%20doing%20more%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20project%20manager%20for%20six%20years.%20It's%20a%20lot%20of%20coordination.%20In%202021%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20working%20two%20jobs%20simultaneously.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20didn't%20research%20whether%20I%20was%20allowed%20to%20do%20it%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20was%20a%20big%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20underestimated%20how%20seriously%20my%20employer%20would%20take%20my%20second%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20full-time%20job%20at%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20games%20company%20called%20Hunt%20A%20Killer%20when%20I%20got%20a%20contract%20with%20Apple.%20I%20was%20super%20excited%20about%20it%20because%20everybody%20knows%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20wasn't%20concerned%20about%20what%20my%20other%20company%20would%20think.%20But%20I%20soon%20realized%20I%20had%20underestimated%20how%20seriously%20they%20would%20take%20it.%20I%20updated%20my%20LinkedIn%20and%20people%20at%20my%20current%20company%20started%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20going%20on%3F%20She%20posted%20that%20she%20is%20working%20another%20job.%20Did%20she%20leave%3F%20Is%20she%20leaving%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20approached%20me%20and%20wanted%20to%20know%20what%20was%20going%20on.%20It%20was%20an%20awkward%20conversation.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20going%20to%20get%20fired.%20They%20made%20it%20sound%20like%20I%20was%20stealing%20company%20time%2C%20which%20I%20wasn't.%20There%20are%20168%20hours%20in%20a%20week%2C%20so%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%2080%20hours%2C%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20doing%20all%20the%20work%20assigned%20to%20me%2C%20but%20they%20felt%20like%20they%20weren't%20getting%20enough%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%2C%20so%20they%20started%20giving%20me%20more%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20if%20I%20did%20this%20again%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20keep%20it%20a%20secret%20and%20lay%20low.%20After%20the%20Apple%20contract%20ended%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20July%202022%2C%20I%20also%20left%20my%20full-time%20job%20at%20Hunt%20A%20Killer%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20job-hop%20often%20and%20always%20look%20out%20for%20new%20contract%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20another%20full-time%20job%20and%20a%20contract%20lined%20up%20at%20companies%20where%20nobody%20knew%20me.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20typically%20job-hop%20after%20a%20year%20or%20when%20the%20contract%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20working%20in%20this%20way%20since%202022%20on%20and%20off.%20I%20try%20not%20to%20go%20more%20than%20six%20months%20without%20at%20least%20a%20part-time%20job%20on%20the%20side.%20I've%20done%20project%20management%20jobs%20in%20tech%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20retail%20for%20companies%20like%20Apple%2C%20Hunt%20A%20Killer%2C%20and%20Rakuten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20never%20had%20two%20full-time%20permanent%20jobs%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20it's%20too%20much%20of%20a%20commitment%20and%20feels%20more%20risky.%20I've%20been%20at%20my%20current%20job%20for%2011%20months.%20I'm%20enjoying%20it%2C%20so%20I'll%20probably%20stay%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3%20jobs%20at%20once%20was%20my%20limit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20worked%20three%20jobs%20at%20once%20for%20about%20three%20months.%20I%20had%20a%20full-time%20job%20and%20two%20contracts%2C%20one%20full-time%20and%20one%20part-time.%20I%20worked%20between%2070%20and%2080%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20and%20my%20working%20day%20was%20usually%20from%207%20a.m.%20to%207%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20on%20the%20East%20Coast%2C%20and%20one%20of%20my%20jobs%20is%20often%20on%20the%20West%20Coast.%20I%20don't%20always%20have%20jobs%20on%20opposite%20coasts%2C%20but%20it's%20my%20preferred%20way%20of%20working.%20I%20would%20wake%20up%20early%20and%20do%20my%20East%20Coast%20work.%20By%202%20p.m.%2C%20I'd%20start%20doing%20my%20West%20Coast%20job%20until%20around%207%20p.m.%20or%208%20p.m.%20It%20got%20a%20bit%20overwhelming%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20exhausted%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGenerally%2C%20I%20work%2012%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20have%20a%20job%20on%20each%20coast%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20generally%20check%20if%20I'm%20legally%20allowed%20to%20work%20another%20job%20before%20taking%20it%20on%20now.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20work%20for%20two%20competing%20companies%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20a%20legal%20disaster%20waiting%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20generally%20work%20between%2010%20and%2012%20hours%20a%20day.%20I%20wake%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%2C%20work%20out%20and%20have%20breakfast.%20I%20usually%20have%20all%20my%20meetings%20for%20one%20job%20between%208%20a.m.%20and%2011%20a.m.%20If%20a%20job%20is%20on%20the%20West%20Coast%2C%20I%20have%20meetings%20for%20those%20jobs%20from%20around%20lunchtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeetings%20for%20different%20jobs%20rarely%20overlapped%2C%20but%20it%20did%20happen.%20I'd%20have%20to%20juggle%20muting%2C%20volumes%2C%20and%20cameras.%20I%20didn't%20usually%20have%20to%20speak%20in%20both%2C%20so%20it%20worked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20take%20breaks%20and%20take%20a%20quick%20walk%20but%20generally%20eat%20lunch%20at%20my%20desk.%20Once%20my%20meetings%20are%20over%2C%20I%20return%20to%20the%20East%20Coast%20job%20and%20do%20emails%20and%20other%20desk%20work.%20Then%2C%20I%20do%20the%20same%20for%20the%20West%20Coast%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20each%20job%20in%20chunks%20rather%20than%20both%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20confuse%20things.%20I%20have%20separate%20laptops%20and%20whichever%20one%20I'm%20not%20working%20on%2C%20I'll%20close%20it%20or%20put%20it%20over%20to%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERed%20flags%20for%20me%20are%20in-person%20meetings%20or%20mandatory%20hours%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20applying%20for%20jobs%2C%20in-person%20meetings%2C%20micromanagement%2C%20or%20mandatory%20hours%20are%20red%20flags.%20If%20you're%20on%20a%20salary%2C%20you%20can%20fly%20under%20the%20radar%20as%20long%20as%20you're%20getting%20your%20work%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20don't%20know%20when%20I'm%20working%20as%20long%20as%20I%20attend%20meetings.%20They%20just%20know%20that%20it's%20done.%20Apart%20from%20that%20first%20job%20where%20they%20found%20out%2C%20no%20one%20has%20ever%20complained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20file%20regular%20W-2%20taxes%2C%20and%20my%20filing%20status%20has%20never%20changed.%20I%20don't%20register%20my%20jobs%20differently.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20was%20initially%20nervous%20about%20the%20legality.%20But%20if%20my%20bosses%20don't%20have%20any%20reason%20to%20look%20into%20it%2C%20they%20probably%20won't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20multiple%20resumes%20highlighting%20different%20skills%20and%20jobs%20rather%20than%20listing%20all%20my%20jobs%20simultaneously.%20If%20it%20ever%20does%20come%20up%2C%20I%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20the%20dates%20overlap%20less%20than%20they%20did.%20The%20only%20time%20I%20was%20asked%20about%20overlap%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20I%20didn't%20get%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20happy%20working%20like%20this%20to%20maintain%20my%20lifestyle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20happy%20working%20like%20this.%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20super%20busy%20social%20life.%20I'm%20more%20introverted.%20I%20have%20a%20reputation%20among%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20for%20working%20multiple%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20I%20would%20be%20able%20to%20have%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20I%20want%20without%20having%20done%20it.%20I%20bought%20a%20house%20in%202022%20after%20saving%20%2430%2C000%20in%20four%20months%20while%20working%20three%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20goal%20of%20buying%20a%20house%20kept%20me%20motivated.%20It%20would%20have%20taken%20me%20years%20to%20do%20that%20without%20doing%20multiple%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20sold%20this%20American%20dream%2C%20but%20how%20can%20you%20achieve%20it%20with%20inflation%2C%20a%20pandemic%2C%20layoffs%2C%20and%20all%20these%20other%20things%3F%20The%20only%20way%20is%20to%20beat%20the%20system%2C%20find%20a%20loophole%2C%20and%20get%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20feel%20secure%20having%20one%20job%20in%20the%20current%20landscape%20with%20AI%20and%20layoffs.%20The%20companies%20will%20do%20what's%20best%20for%20them%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20do%20what's%20best%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-employed-double-dip-how-to-work-multiple-jobs-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712744272000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66165c5e1caec1275a6e7126%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-employed-double-dip-how-to-work-multiple-jobs-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Overemployed%20millennial%20project%20manager%20Kendall%20McGill%20often%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20dips%2C%26quot%3B%20picking%20up%20extra%20work%20on%20contract%20alongside%20her%20full-time%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Isabelle%20Aron)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-employed-double-dip-how-to-work-multiple-jobs-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Search%20after%20deadly%20blast%20at%20Italian%20power%20plant%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712744113000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F12CDD%2Fproduction%2F_133112077_vigili2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68761493%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20pe